---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Now | The Void"
  description="What Miguel Marin Vermelho is currently working on, reading, and thinking about."
>
  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto py-20 px-6">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-garden-accent dark:text-garden-dark-accent font-ui text-sm font-medium tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">Now</p>
      <h1 class="text-garden-primary dark:text-garden-dark-primary mb-4">What I'm doing now</h1>
      <p class="text-muted font-ui text-sm">Last updated: March 2026 · Inspired by <a href="https://nownownow.com/about" class="underline hover:no-underline text-garden-accent dark:text-garden-dark-accent" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">nownownow.com</a></p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-lg dark:prose-dark max-w-none space-y-12">

      <section>
        <h2>Work</h2>
        <p>
          I'm CTO at <a href="https://flown.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">FLOWN</a> — a science-backed deep work platform that brings people together for focused coworking sessions and expert-led workshops. My work sits at the intersection of product, engineering leadership, and the research on human attention and performance that FLOWN is built on.
        </p>
        <p>
          Most days involve TypeScript, React, and Next.js — but the part I find most interesting is the product thinking: how do you design digital environments that actually help people focus rather than fragment their attention?
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Reading</h2>
        <p>
          Working through Nāgārjuna's <em>Mūlamadhyamakakārikā</em> slowly — the philosophy of emptiness keeps revealing new depths the more I sit with it. Alongside that, Ryuichi Sakamoto's final album <em>12</em>, which isn't a book but feels like one: 12 pieces of music recorded while he was terminally ill, each one a meditation on time and presence.
        </p>
        <p>
          On the technical side, diving into AI agent patterns and what "agentic" software actually means in practice versus the hype.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Thinking about</h2>
        <p>
          The question I keep returning to: what does it mean to be present in a world designed to pull you away from the present? FLOWN works on this from a productivity angle, but the garden is where I explore the philosophical and contemplative dimensions.
        </p>
        <p>
          Also thinking about multilingualism as a way of seeing — how switching between Portuguese, English, Spanish, French, and Japanese isn't just a communication skill but a different lens on experience. Each language encodes different intuitions about time, relationship, and responsibility.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Making</h2>
        <p>
          This garden. Adding posts slowly and tending the connections between them. The goal isn't to publish frequently but to think carefully, and let the writing be evidence of the thinking rather than a performance of it.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
